#euclidean method:calculate the euclidean distance between usernames

#create a matrix(euclidean_dist), using data from dfmat

#according to unique username to divide euclidean_dist into diffferent groups

#calulate the similarity between documents, “margin” means consider what to calculate similarity

#keep the first 5 columns and volumns

euclidean_dist <- dfmat %>%
  dfm_group(groups = username) %>%
  textstat_dist(margin = "documents", method = "euclidean")

euclidean_dist[1:5,1:5]

#create a matrix

euclidmat <- as.matrix(euclidean_dist)

#convert rows to columns and reassign to cosmatdf

#visualize

#ggplot:based on this dataset

#geom_point: x axis reordered username and rank username from high to low (according to euclidean distance), y axis is the value of euclidean distance

#coord_flip: this section flips the axes and swaps the x and y axes to better show the horizontal labels.

#x and y lab: names

#theme_minimal: topic

ggplot(euclidmatdf) +
  geom_point(aes(x=reorder(username, -corr_may), y= corr_may)) + 
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("MP username") +
  ylab("Euclidean score") + 
  theme_minimal()

#complexity

#create speeches dataset

speeches  <- readRDS(gzcon(url("https://github.com/cjbarrie/CTA-ED/blob/main/data/comparison-complexity/speeches.rds?raw=true")))

#coleman-liau

used coleman-liau measure to calculats speeches text’s complexity

#extract outcome from dataset, and stroed in coleman.liau

speeches$coleman.liau <- textstat_readability(speeches$text, measure = "Coleman.Liau")
speeches$coleman.liau <- speeches$coleman.liau$Coleman.Liau

#create corpus dataset

#used speakers as group criteria

#calculate mean, standard deviation, how many speakers

calsulate every speaker’s standard error, confidence interval(95%)

sum_corpus <- speeches %>%
  group_by(speaker) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(coleman.liau, na.rm=TRUE),
                   SD=sd(coleman.liau, na.rm=TRUE),
                   N=length(speaker))

sum_corpus$se <- sum_corpus$SD / sqrt(sum_corpus$N)
sum_corpus$min <- sum_corpus$mean - 1.96*sum_corpus$se
sum_corpus$max <- sum_corpus$mean + 1.96*sum_corpus$se
sum_corpus
## # A tibble: 4 × 7
##   speaker          mean    SD     N    se   min   max
##   <chr>           <dbl> <dbl> <int> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 D. Cameron       49.4  3.95   456 0.185  49.0  49.8
## 2 G. Brown         47.6  4.43   277 0.266  47.0  48.1
## 3 J.L.R. Zapatero  43.5  4.05   354 0.215  43.0  43.9
## 4 M. Rajoy         46.5  5.08   389 0.257  46.0  47.0

#visualize

#stat = “identity” means the mean for each speaker is shown directly as the height of the bar chart

#geom_errorbar: represents the standard deviation of the Coleman-Liau index mean for each speaker.

ggplot(sum_corpus, aes(x = speaker, y = mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "skyblue", color = "black") + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - SD, ymax = mean + SD), width = 0.2, color = "black") +
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("Speaker") +
  ylab("Mean Complexity") +
  theme_minimal()

#automated readability index

speeches$ari <- textstat_readability(speeches$text, measure = "ARI")
speeches$ari <- speeches$ari$ARI
sum_corpus <- speeches %>%
  group_by(speaker) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(ari, na.rm=TRUE),
                   SD=sd(ari, na.rm=TRUE),
                   N=length(speaker))

sum_corpus$se <- sum_corpus$SD / sqrt(sum_corpus$N)
sum_corpus$min <- sum_corpus$mean - 1.96*sum_corpus$se
sum_corpus$max <- sum_corpus$mean + 1.96*sum_corpus$se
sum_corpus
